@Limess a few questions

- for this dataset do you want to run bulkinsert or upsert? if it's append only dataset, then bulkinsert should be the mode
- does smaller parquet files matter a lot in this case? `GLOBAL_SORT` is expected to use more diskspace as it does a shuffling sort to line up records for bulk writing. If you change to `NONE` sort mode, you'd get more more small files but faster write and less disk spill. Small files can be mitigated by clustering. There is some trade-off to consider based on your needs.
- 10036 parallelism may be a bit too high; some number around 3600 = # executors x # cores x 2 ?

